ou don't need to do this send-time PGP signature, and git<br />will now verify (and save) the signature automatically.<br /><br />See<br />  <a href="https://lkml.org/lkml/2011/12/14/543">https://lkml.org/lkml/2011/12/14/543</a><br /><br />that I sent to Ted about how it ends up looking - you can check out<br />that commit 2240a7bb479c with "git show" and "git cat-file commit" to<br />see how your signature would be archived and saved without actually<br />being bothersome when just looking at the history.<br /><br />                  Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
